Maintainer: Russ Allbery <rra@debian.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4), libkrb5-dev, libopenafs-dev, libldap2-dev
Standards-Version: 3.7.2
Homepage: http://www.eyrie.org/~eagle/software/krb5-sync/

Package: krb5-sync
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${perl:Depends}
Recommends: krb5-admin-server
Description: MIT Kerberos KDC plugin for password synchronization
 This plugin synchronizes passwords changed via kadmind to a foreign
 realm via the Kerberos v5 password change protocol (primarily implemented
 by Active Directory) and via AFS calls to a Kerberos v4 kaserver.  It can
 also propagate changes to DISALLOW_ALL_TIX flag to Windows AD.
